@page "/enigma-game-mechanics"

<SeoHead Title="Enigma Game Mechanics | Rooms, Puzzles, Rewards, and Maps"
         Description="Learn the core mechanics behind room progression, puzzle states, map ownership, item usage, and economy-linked progression."
         OpenGraphType="article"
         SchemaType="Article"
         Keywords="Enigma mechanics, room puzzles, Maze Nuggets, map discovery, puzzle systems" />

<div class="content seo-page-shell">
    <section class="panel seo-page-hero">
        <span class="profile-kicker">Mechanics</span>
        <h1>Enigma Game Mechanics</h1>
        <p>Enigma combines direct movement, room-based puzzle states, persistent map ownership, and economy systems that carry progression between runs.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Room Structure</h2>
        <h3>Start, Reward, and Finish Rooms</h3>
        <p>Every maze includes a start room, finish room, and intermediate rooms. Layout and door connectivity are generated from the seed.</p>
        <h3>In-Room Interaction</h3>
        <p>Most interactions happen directly on the stage. Console overlays appear only when precision puzzle input is needed.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Puzzle Systems</h2>
        <h3>Stage Puzzles</h3>
        <p>Spatial mechanics like pressure plates, route checks, and activation zones are solved directly inside the room.</p>
        <h3>Overlay Puzzles</h3>
        <p>Logic, memory, and timing variants open in the room console and return results to the shared room state.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Map Lifecycle</h2>
        <h3>Discovery and Ownership</h3>
        <p>Map discovery is tied to real completion. Ownership can transfer later through marketplace actions without rewriting the original discovery history.</p>
        <h3>Listing, Analysis, and Locks</h3>
        <p>Owned maps can be listed on the marketplace or assigned to analysis for daily MN. Maps under analysis are lock-protected and cannot be sold or recycled until lock conditions expire.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Progression and Power</h2>
        <h3>MN and Item Flow</h3>
        <p>Run outcomes, daily systems, and economy interactions update your MN balance and inventory availability.</p>
        <h3>Governance Weighting</h3>
        <p>Voting power is based on MN spent and a capped multiplier model that factors staked maps and participation history.</p>
    </section>
</div>
